‘ Semper novum' is, in my judgment, an interpolation, for this epithet was, 01 course, quite as applicable to the audiences of the speaker's own day as to those of the Republic. Hence the phrase has no place in the present context, which deals only with points of differ-enee between the two periods. This suspicion derives strong external support from the fact that the MS. variants (p. 45) also unmistakably point to a supralinear gloss which subsequently intruded into the text in different places.
